column6: The server connection times out frequently, causing disruptions in service.
The network performance is significantly slower than usual, affecting user productivity.
The storage capacity has reached its limit, and there is no more space available for data storage.
During voice calls, the connection frequently drops, leading to communication issues.
Data integrity is compromised, resulting in corrupted files and incorrect information.
The application crashes randomly, causing inconvenience and data loss.
Users are unable to reset their passwords, preventing access to their accounts.
The printers connected to the network are not being detected by the devices.
Emails are experiencing delays in delivery, impacting timely communication.
The software is not compatible with the latest operating system, causing errors and malfunctions.
